The paper focuses on identifying and analyzing design smells in software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of a tool for analyzing large volumes of source code suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD). The study also involves statistical analysis, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) if the analysis involves identifying potential security vulnerabilities.
